      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "Ask if the patient is currently taking any medications. \nA brief list is sufficient — the full details will be \ncollected on the intake forms.\n\nSay something like: \"Are you currently taking any \nmedications? Just a quick overview is fine — we'll \nget the full list on your intake forms.\"\n\nIf the user lists medications: Acknowledge without \nrepeating every one back: \"Got it, I've noted those \ndown.\" If it's a short list (1-3), you can read them \nback. If it's a long list, just confirm: \"Okay, that's \nquite a few — I've got them noted and the doctor will \ngo through everything in detail at your visit.\"\n\nIf the user says none: \"Perfect, no medications — \ngot it.\"\n\nIf the user says \"just vitamins\" or \"only supplements\": \n\"Got it — we'll note that. The doctor may ask for \nspecifics at your visit but that's all I need for now.\"\n\nIf the user can't remember all of them: \"That's totally \nfine — just name whatever comes to mind. You can bring \nthe full list or your pill bottles to the visit and \nthe team will go through them.\"\n\nIf the user says they'd rather share at the visit or \non the forms: \"No problem — we'll collect everything \non the intake paperwork.\"\n\nIf the user doesn't want to share: \"I understand — \nthis is just so the doctor has a heads-up. But you \ncan absolutely save it for the intake forms.\"\n\nOne ask is enough. Do NOT push for completeness — \nthe intake forms and the visit itself will capture \nthe full picture."
      }
    },
